caller_intent: The caller is seeking clarification about their renters insurance coverage, specifically whether it protects personal belongings, and is concerned about the landlord's new insurance policy not covering tenant property.
resolution_steps: Brandi confirms the caller's renters insurance policy covers personal belongings up to $25,000.
Explains the difference between landlord's property insurance (covering the building) and the caller's renters insurance (covering personal items).
Mentions annual policy review process to adjust coverage as needed.
Offers assistance with car insurance inquiry, though the conversation is cut off.
knowledge_required: Renters insurance policy details (coverage limits, personal property protection)
summary: The caller was concerned about their renters insurance coverage after learning the landlord's new policy doesn't protect tenant belongings. Brandi clarified their policy covers personal items up to $25,000 and explained annual review options. The caller also expressed interest in discussing car insurance, though the conversation was cut off.
